 A MAN has been arrested following an alleged assault at a subway station . 
 A 45-year-old man was taken to the Glasgow Royal Infirmary and treated for an eye injury after an incident which started when he bumped into another man at Glasgow's Buchanan Street station at around 8.10am on Monday. 
Police scanned CCTV footage taken in the station to try and identify the suspect, who was seen leaving Buchanan Street underground and head towards Buchanan Galleries shopping centre.
 British Transport Police said a 25-year-old man had been arrested and a report will be sent to the procurator fiscal. 
